<TEXT>
<P>
 Abel Anton of Spain surged past Vincent Rousseau of Belgium with only 10 yards 
left to win the 10,000 meters at track and field's European Championships at 
Helsinki. 
</P>
<P>
 Aton's winning time was a personal-best 28 minutes 06.03 seconds. Rousseau's 
time was 28:06.63. 
