SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Natural Gas Facility Opens: The nation's largest facility for converting cars 
and trucks to natural gas opens in East Los Angeles on Friday. The Ecotrans 
assembly plant, owned in part by Southern California Gas Co., is one of the 
first enterprises to begin to meet a growing demand for cleaner, 
alternative-fuel cars, largely created by the California Air Resources Board 
Low Emission Vehicle rules. While most attention has been focused on electric 
cars, many thousands more natural gas vehicles, particularly in fleet use, are 
expected to appear on the state's highways over the next few years. 
</P>
