<P>
PEOPLE: FLUOR VICE CHAIRMAN KONTNY TAKING EARLY RETIREMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fluor Corp. said Vice Chairman Vince Kontny has decided to take early 
retirement after 29 years with the Irvine-based engineering and construction 
company. Kontny, 57, said he is looking forward to spending extra time with his 
family and on other interests. "I have mixed emotions about leaving at this 
particular time, given the company's considerable success, exceptional 
financial condition and positive business outlook," said Kontny. 
</P>
