SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irvine Co. Negotiates Swap: Discussions are expected to continue this week 
between Orange County's largest private landowner and the Department of 
Interior regarding a possible land swap in which the development giant could 
gain control of all or part of El Toro Marine Corps Air Station in exchange for 
property bordering the Cleveland National Forest.Federal officials were in 
Orange County two weeks ago meeting with Irvine Co. executives about the 
proposal for future control of the 4,700-acre military base, which is scheduled 
to close in 1999, according to officials. It is unknown whether such an 
enormous swap would boost or hinder prospects for building a commercial airport 
at El Toro. 
</P>
