<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; COLLEGE GETS FUNDS FOR COMPUTER LAB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College professor Wayne Gibson has won a $30,000 grant to buy 
math-related computers and software to improve undergraduate science courses. 
</P>
<P>
 The award, from the National Science Foundation, will be used to create a 
computer laboratory that will free students from tough algebraic calculations 
so they can concentrate on the underlying concepts of experiments. 
</P>
<P>
 The lab will also offer multimedia presentations that explain complex calculus 
concepts in an easy-to-understand manner, spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is intended to meet the special needs of the Rancho Santiago 
campus. More than 50% of its students speak English as a second language, and 
almost 70% of incoming freshmen place below average on standard math placement 
exams, Ruhe said.JON NALICK 
</P>
