<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; CITY WILL BUY OLD FIRE STATION SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has decided to buy the Old San Juan Capistrano Fire Station site from 
the county. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council voted last week to pay $265,000 for the property at 31411 La 
Matanza St., where the city operates community services programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1982, the city had been leasing buildings on the site for $1 a year, but 
the county told city officials this year that the arrangement would be ending 
for financial reasons. 
</P>
<P>
 The city had the option of buying the property or paying fair market rent, 
according to Cynthia Pendleton, the city's administrative services director. 
</P>
<P>
 Pendleton said the monthly payments to buy the property will be significantly 
lower than rent would have been. The property is being financed at 8% over 30 
years. 
</P>
<P>
 If the city ever develops the property for commercial use, the county is to 
receive 80% of the revenue generated. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
