<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOODS WINS MAJOR EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tiger Woods birdied the second hole and never trailed Sunday as he defeated 
Chris Riley, 2 and 1, to win the match play championship at the 92nd Western 
Amateur golf tournament Sunday at Point O Woods Golf and Country Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Woods, 18, of Cypress moved to a 3-up lead with consecutive birdies on the 
10th and 11th holes.Riley, 20, of San Diego, birdied the 14th hole to cut 
Woods' lead to 2-up, but Woods halved the next three holes to post the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 "This win means a lot to me," Woods said. "All the big tournaments I've won 
until now have been junior tournaments. This is a great tournament on a great 
golf course. It really is the Masters of amateur golf." 
</P>
<P>
 In Sunday morning's semifinals, Woods defeated Darron Stiles of Plant City, 
Fla., 5 and 3, and Riley topped Alan Bratton of College Station, Tex., 3 and 2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
