<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. WOMEN, REMAINING PERFECT IN GOODWILL BASKETBALL, TAKE GOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. women's basketball team, getting 18 points from Lisa Leslie, won its 
first gold medal in a major championship in four years by beating France, 
87-63, Sunday at the Goodwill Games. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the third consecutive gold medal in the Goodwill Games for the U.S. 
women, who have a 14-0 record since the competition began in 1986.The Americans 
took the gold that year, and again in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 It was their first gold medal since the 1990 world championships, however. 
Sheryl Swoopes added 14 points for the Americans. Dawn Staley, Ruthie 
Bolton-Holifield and Shanda Berry had 11 points each. 
</P>
<P>
 Catherine Melain led France with 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
 The United States led from the start, building a 39-19 lead at halftime. The 
closest the French came in the second half was a 17-point deficit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
