<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. CARDINALS IN REGIONAL FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County Cardinals won two games Sunday to advance to the title game 
of the Connie Mack Pacific Region Championship in Cherry Creek, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cardinals beat the Lafayette (Calif.) Generals, 16-3, and the Albuquerque 
(N.M.) Rebels, 10-6. Orange County is undefeated in the double-elimination 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Greg Hanioan was six for seven, scored four runs and drove in two in the two 
games for the Cardinals, who play Lafayette again today for a chance to advance 
to Connie Mack World Series in Farmington, N.M. 
</P>
</TEXT>
