<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPLASH START TRIP WITH A VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Splash, starting a seven-game trip on a positive note, beat the Arizona 
Sandsharks, 5-4, Sunday in a Continental Indoor Soccer League game before 4,875 
at the America West Arena in Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
 After being shut out in the first quarter, Anaheim (14-5) scored three goals 
in the second and third to take a 3-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Raffaele Ruotolo and Armando Valdivia scored the first two goals of the fourth 
quarter to give the Splash a 5-2 lead, before Arizona (7-10) made it close. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruotolo had an assist, increasing his record streak to 20 games. Dale Ervine 
was held without a goal for the first time in 10 games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
