<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NYELAND ACRES; VICTIM OF FATAL STABBING IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County coroner's officials have identified the Nyeland Acres man who 
was stabbed to death during an argument with his roommate. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Jesus Arredondo-Sanchez, 31, an employee at Vic's Novelty store in 
Oxnard, died at St. John's Regional Medical Center a short time after the 10:15 
p.m. incident Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Arredondo-Sanchez's roommate, Miguel Garabaldi, 38, following 
the stabbing. Garabaldi had first fled the scene but returned later to turn 
himself in. 
</P>
<P>
 He is scheduled to be arraigned in Ventura County Municipal Court on Tuesday 
on a homicide charge. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the two men were drinking beer and watching television 
Friday night when they apparently began arguing. Garabaldi picked up a kitchen 
knife and stabbed Arredondo-Sanchez once in the stomach, police said. JEFF 
McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
