<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN HIT BY TRUCK IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Santa Ana man was in critical condition Sunday at St. John's Regional 
Medical Center after being hit by a truck as he stood outside his disabled 
vehicle along Oxnard Boulevard, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gerald Buxton, 62, was outside his Toyota Landcruiser on Oxnard Boulevard just 
north of Orchard Place on Saturday evening when a small truck driven by David 
Christopher Estey, 27, of Thousand Oaks slammed into Buxton and his vehicle, 
Oxnard police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Buxton, a minister, was thrown 90 feet and landed on the sidewalk with severe 
internal injuries, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said Estey lost control of his car after the impact and ran over 
the sidewalk before coming to rest in a drainage ditch. 
</P>
<P>
 Estey, who was not injured, was arrested on suspicion of felony drunken 
driving. He was released after posting a $5,000 bond and is scheduled to be 
arraigned Aug. 19 in Ventura County Municipal Court. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
