<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIVAL GANGS BRAWL IN VENTURA PARKING LOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two rival street gangs clashed Sunday night in a convenience store parking lot 
in Ventura's Montalvo area, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dozens of Ventura police officers and Ventura County sheriff's deputies 
responded to the store in the 6300 block of Bristol Road around 8 p.m. after 
receiving several 911 emergency calls. 
</P>
<P>
 When officers arrived, they encountered some 25 to 30 suspected gang members 
involved in a brawl. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers quickly stopped the fight, but because none of those fighting would 
press charges, no arrests were made. 
</P>
<P>
 A Ventura police spokesman said those who were fighting were detained, 
interviewed, photographed and released at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Two people involved in the melee apparently were injured, but refused medical 
assistance. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said a toy handgun was recovered but that no weapons were discovered. 
No officers were injured during the incident. J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
