<HEADLINE>
<P>
5 PARTY-GOERS INJURED IN GANG SHOOTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Five people were injured during a weekend shootout between rival gangs, police 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Two parties at houses in the 9500 block of Amboy Avenue got out of control at 
about 10:35 p.m. Saturday when party-goers at one house threw bottles into the 
yard of the house next door, said Officer Don Cox of the Los Angeles Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Party-goers at the second house, Cox said, retaliated by shooting into the 
crowd of about 200 people in the yard of the neighboring house. Five youths 
between the ages of 16 and 20 were hit, Cox said, although no one suffered 
life-threatening injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities did not release the names and ages of the victims, who included 
both males and females. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are continuing to search for the attackers, Cox said. 
</P>
