<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTY FIREFIGHTERS STOP BLAZE IN GARAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County firefighters extinguished a garage fire in Oak View early 
Sunday after neighbors reported seeing smoke coming from the area. 
</P>
<P>
 Three dozen firefighters responded to 74 Calle Cinco de Mayo about 9:40 a.m. 
Sunday, putting out the blaze within 20 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
 "It never got to the house," said Tracy Valencia, a county Fire Department 
spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials discovered ammunition inside the garage, but investigators were 
unable to immediately determine whether it played a part in starting the fire, 
Valencia said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the blaze, and no damage estimate was available, 
officials said. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
